        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 9 at 3:16AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 315 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Campo, or 23 miles north of Boise City, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Keyes and Sturgis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
